00:23:07.715 --> 00:23:08.840 align:middle line:90%
in the middle of the ocean.

00:23:08.840 --> 00:23:11.520 align:middle line:84%
I mean there is definitely an
environmental crisis going on,

00:23:11.520 --> 00:23:13.600 align:middle line:90%
I believe.

00:23:13.600 --> 00:23:16.620 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: I believe so-- I
mean, actually I'm not sure.

00:23:16.620 --> 00:23:18.030 align:middle line:84%
Let's say there
is-- I don't have

00:23:18.030 --> 00:23:19.950 align:middle line:90%
any problems saying there is.

00:23:19.950 --> 00:23:25.710 align:middle line:84%
The question is, if we were
somehow to reduce carbon,

00:23:25.710 --> 00:23:29.235 align:middle line:84%
because that's what they
point to is specifically

00:23:29.235 --> 00:23:32.160 align:middle line:84%
man-made carbon
emissions, would that

00:23:32.160 --> 00:23:34.650 align:middle line:84%
make a difference on
this warming trend?

00:23:34.650 --> 00:23:39.490 align:middle line:84%
My scientific research, as
well as many others, say no.

00:23:39.490 --> 00:23:42.590 align:middle line:84%
Is our pollution having
a marginal effect?

00:23:42.590 --> 00:23:48.025 align:middle line:84%
Yes, but my data is saying one,
two, three five percent, not--

00:23:48.025 --> 00:23:53.040 align:middle line:84%
Al Gore, James Hansen, and
global warming et al say 100%.

00:23:53.040 --> 00:23:54.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, what
about-- our listeners

00:23:54.920 --> 00:23:58.420 align:middle line:84%
are asking about the melting
of the ice caps, various things

00:23:58.420 --> 00:24:00.060 align:middle line:84%
that are attributed
to global warming.

00:24:00.060 --> 00:24:01.730 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Yeah,
unfortunately, that's

00:24:01.730 --> 00:24:03.610 align:middle line:90%
happened many times before.

00:24:03.610 --> 00:24:05.887 align:middle line:90%
The Earth goes through cycles.

00:24:05.887 --> 00:24:07.970 align:middle line:84%
I'm not denying we're in
a warming trend-- there's

00:24:07.970 --> 00:24:10.310 align:middle line:84%
warming trends and
cooling trends.

00:24:10.310 --> 00:24:12.150 align:middle line:84%
We're in a warming
trend right now.

00:24:12.150 --> 00:24:14.140 align:middle line:84%
Some scientists and
people are happy we

00:24:14.140 --> 00:24:16.790 align:middle line:84%
are, that we're not
freezing right now.

00:24:16.790 --> 00:24:18.517 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is there a
cooling trend coming?

00:24:18.517 --> 00:24:19.350 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: Absolutely.

00:24:19.350 --> 00:24:20.266 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: At what point?

00:24:20.266 --> 00:24:23.240 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Some believe
it's already started.

00:24:23.240 --> 00:24:25.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I've heard
that, as well,

00:24:25.250 --> 00:24:26.685 align:middle line:84%
but how long do
these trends last?

00:24:26.685 --> 00:24:28.560 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: I don't think
there's anyone number.

00:24:28.560 --> 00:24:31.960 align:middle line:84%
I think there are cycles within
cycles, cycles that supersede

00:24:31.960 --> 00:24:34.956 align:middle line:84%
cycles-- to take the
solar cycle, for example,

00:24:34.956 --> 00:24:37.120 align:middle line:84%
there's an 11-year
cycle, 22-year cycle.

00:24:37.120 --> 00:24:41.800 align:middle line:84%
We hear about the 100-year
floods, there's 100-year cycle,

00:24:41.800 --> 00:24:46.960 align:middle line:84%
2,300-year-- I don't
know what cycle we're in.

00:24:46.960 --> 00:24:47.569 align:middle line:90%
Hard to say--

00:24:47.569 --> 00:24:48.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting

00:24:48.360 --> 00:24:50.760 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Possibly we
might make some headway

00:24:50.760 --> 00:24:52.475 align:middle line:84%
into finding out
where we are, but I

00:24:52.475 --> 00:24:54.100 align:middle line:84%
think that's exactly
what's happening--

00:24:54.100 --> 00:24:55.230 align:middle line:90%
we are in that cycle.

00:24:55.230 --> 00:24:57.960 align:middle line:84%
I do want to make the statement,
because so many people

00:24:57.960 --> 00:25:02.680 align:middle line:84%
misunderstand me, I
would say there's not

00:25:02.680 --> 00:25:06.990 align:middle line:84%
a lot of people who do more
for environment than I do.

00:25:06.990 --> 00:25:10.940 align:middle line:84%
I'm from Seattle, and Seattle
is very conscious of recycling,

00:25:10.940 --> 00:25:15.720 align:middle line:84%
the whole bit, very clean
parks, people do a great job.

00:25:15.720 --> 00:25:19.610 align:middle line:84%
I don't know anyone, not
one person, honestly,

00:25:19.610 --> 00:25:21.500 align:middle line:90%
who's pro pollution.

00:25:21.500 --> 00:25:24.570 align:middle line:84%
I go further and say if you
find one, put him in jail,

00:25:24.570 --> 00:25:25.500 align:middle line:90%
I could care less.

00:25:25.500 --> 00:25:27.160 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I'm really glad
you said that, actually,

00:25:27.160 --> 00:25:28.905 align:middle line:84%
because there are a
lot of efforts that

00:25:28.905 --> 00:25:31.810 align:middle line:84%
are going towards recycling, a
lot of efforts that are going

00:25:31.810 --> 00:25:34.040 align:middle line:84%
towards cleaning up our
planet, and that absolutely

00:25:34.040 --> 00:25:37.050 align:middle line:84%
has nothing to do with the whole
global warming conversation

00:25:37.050 --> 00:25:38.830 align:middle line:84%
that the scientific
community is having--

00:25:38.830 --> 00:25:40.720 align:middle line:90%
it's about responsibility.

00:25:40.720 --> 00:25:42.160 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: I think
that's wonderful.

00:25:42.160 --> 00:25:44.650 align:middle line:84%
The environmentalists
that I know,

00:25:44.650 --> 00:25:48.040 align:middle line:84%
the ones who know
about permaculture,

00:25:48.040 --> 00:25:50.520 align:middle line:84%
who know about
sustainability, who

00:25:50.520 --> 00:25:55.000 align:middle line:84%
know about community gardening--
those are the ones who I think

00:25:55.000 --> 00:25:57.740 align:middle line:90%
got cheated.

00:25:57.740 --> 00:26:01.190 align:middle line:90%
I'm on board with them.

00:26:01.190 --> 00:26:05.420 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if
many other who are

00:26:05.420 --> 00:26:09.500 align:middle line:84%
on what I'll call the global
warming bandwagon even

00:26:09.500 --> 00:26:11.425 align:middle line:90%
understand what's going on.

00:26:11.425 --> 00:26:16.530 align:middle line:84%
Here's the danger-- there's
only so much money we have.

00:26:16.530 --> 00:26:20.750 align:middle line:84%
We can spend it on this
carbon tax thing, which

00:26:20.750 --> 00:26:23.860 align:middle line:90%
gets Al Gore rich, or we can--

00:26:23.860 --> 00:26:26.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How do you really feel?

00:26:26.460 --> 00:26:28.380 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: --or we can
put it towards what

00:26:28.380 --> 00:26:33.330 align:middle line:84%
I believe preparedness
for this warming trend,

00:26:33.330 --> 00:26:35.610 align:middle line:84%
and perhaps a coming
cooling trend,

00:26:35.610 --> 00:26:39.410 align:middle line:84%
and we'd better get
busy, because the IPCC--

00:26:39.410 --> 00:26:41.160 align:middle line:84%
this is where I don't
disagree with them--

00:26:41.160 --> 00:26:46.620 align:middle line:84%
the international consortium
on global warming,

00:26:46.620 --> 00:26:50.230 align:middle line:84%
or climate change,
rather-- they believe that

00:26:50.230 --> 00:26:55.115 align:middle line:84%
as a result of the warming
trend, that some places may

00:26:55.115 --> 00:26:59.260 align:middle line:84%
be flooded-- coastlines,
because of the melt.

00:26:59.260 --> 00:27:01.620 align:middle line:84%
Let's say that's true--
are we really putting

00:27:01.620 --> 00:27:05.067 align:middle line:90%
the effort into migration?

00:27:05.067 --> 00:27:07.650 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There are so many topics
that we could cover here-- it

00:27:07.650 --> 00:27:09.451 align:middle line:84%
has to do with oil
and free energy

00:27:09.451 --> 00:27:10.950 align:middle line:84%
and those types of
things, but we're

00:27:10.950 --> 00:27:12.690 align:middle line:84%
going to talk about
that when we come back.

00:27:12.690 --> 00:27:14.570 align:middle line:84%
We're going to talk
more about understanding

00:27:14.570 --> 00:27:16.490 align:middle line:84%
what the ancient
texts and the Mayans

00:27:16.490 --> 00:27:18.480 align:middle line:84%
have to say about
this trend, as well.

00:27:18.480 --> 00:27:19.490 align:middle line:90%
We'll be right back.

00:27:19.490 --> 00:27:20.170 align:middle line:90%
I'm Lisa Garr.

