00:27:41.070 --> 00:27:43.080 align:middle line:10%
Welcome back, I'm Lisa
Garr, and my guest

00:27:43.080 --> 00:27:45.390 align:middle line:10%
is scientific journalist
Mitch Battros,

00:27:45.390 --> 00:27:47.670 align:middle line:10%
and we're talking
about Earth changes

00:27:47.670 --> 00:27:50.500 align:middle line:10%
and climate change, essentially,
is what we're talking about.

00:27:50.500 --> 00:27:52.890 align:middle line:10%
What do the ancient texts
have to say about this?

00:27:52.890 --> 00:27:56.730 align:middle line:84%
What do the Mayan prophecies
have to say about this?

00:27:56.730 --> 00:28:00.110 align:middle line:10%
>>MITCH: Yes, all of the
ancient texts that most of us

00:28:00.110 --> 00:28:04.100 align:middle line:10%
are aware of actually have
written about climate change

00:28:04.100 --> 00:28:09.440 align:middle line:10%
and cyclical events-- certainly
in the Bible, the Noah flood,

00:28:09.440 --> 00:28:13.980 align:middle line:10%
very well, I think, was
probably a flood, where,

00:28:13.980 --> 00:28:18.630 align:middle line:10%
for whatever reasons, the waters
rise, to who knows how high.

00:28:18.630 --> 00:28:20.590 align:middle line:84%
Other events that
the Earth will shake

00:28:20.590 --> 00:28:24.310 align:middle line:84%
and the buildings are falling
down or temples and so forth,

00:28:24.310 --> 00:28:26.190 align:middle line:84%
earthquakes, and
we certainly know

00:28:26.190 --> 00:28:28.110 align:middle line:84%
about the history
of volcanoes, so I

00:28:28.110 --> 00:28:30.770 align:middle line:84%
think it's clearly been
documented throughout history

00:28:30.770 --> 00:28:36.710 align:middle line:84%
that these cyclical events have
been occurring related to Earth

00:28:36.710 --> 00:28:41.560 align:middle line:84%
changing events, such as this,
and also, some of the ancients

00:28:41.560 --> 00:28:45.130 align:middle line:84%
go further, telling us
about something that's

00:28:45.130 --> 00:28:47.199 align:middle line:84%
coming from the sky
that could be the cause.

00:28:47.199 --> 00:28:49.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And this is what some
of the Mayan texts were saying.

00:28:49.740 --> 00:28:51.379 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: The Mayans especially.

00:28:51.379 --> 00:28:53.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How does the
Vatican come into play

00:28:53.170 --> 00:28:54.070 align:middle line:90%
with all of this?

00:28:54.070 --> 00:28:56.995 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: The Vatican?

00:28:56.995 --> 00:28:58.996 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do they have
something to say about it?

00:28:58.996 --> 00:29:00.290 align:middle line:90%
What does religion have to say?

00:29:00.290 --> 00:29:04.250 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: They do, and it will
be a surprise to most of you,

00:29:04.250 --> 00:29:08.890 align:middle line:84%
I think, being a
Catholic boy myself, I

00:29:08.890 --> 00:29:11.740 align:middle line:84%
was comfortable with it,
but my parents were not.

00:29:11.740 --> 00:29:17.490 align:middle line:10%
It was 1994, I believe it
was, when Pope John Paul

00:29:17.490 --> 00:29:26.290 align:middle line:10%
II came out and said, I'm
paraphrasing, that there should

00:29:26.290 --> 00:29:31.525 align:middle line:10%
be no reason that creation
and evolution can co-exist.

00:29:31.525 --> 00:29:34.700 align:middle line:10%
Now I know that sounds very
simplistic, and many of you

00:29:34.700 --> 00:29:38.550 align:middle line:10%
are maybe saying, duh, but
for the Catholic community,

00:29:38.550 --> 00:29:39.950 align:middle line:10%
that was a shocker.

00:29:39.950 --> 00:29:42.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That they can coexist?

00:29:42.140 --> 00:29:44.180 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: No, that
they-- yeah, the shock

00:29:44.180 --> 00:29:47.420 align:middle line:84%
is that they could coexist,
because the Bible tells us

00:29:47.420 --> 00:29:51.670 align:middle line:84%
that the Earth was created
in seven days, and so on,

00:29:51.670 --> 00:29:53.960 align:middle line:90%
and evolution is blasphemy.

00:29:53.960 --> 00:29:59.470 align:middle line:84%
So to hear the pope,
actually affirm that OK,

00:29:59.470 --> 00:30:01.730 align:middle line:84%
so there's evolution--
big deal, what

00:30:01.730 --> 00:30:04.620 align:middle line:84%
does that have to do anything
with creation and Jesus

00:30:04.620 --> 00:30:05.680 align:middle line:90%
and God?

00:30:05.680 --> 00:30:09.760 align:middle line:84%
So the Vatican has taken
note of things like that,

00:30:09.760 --> 00:30:12.450 align:middle line:84%
and especially with
the new information

00:30:12.450 --> 00:30:15.780 align:middle line:84%
we're getting, because
of the instruments,

00:30:15.780 --> 00:30:19.960 align:middle line:84%
the now pope, Pope
Benedict, actually

00:30:19.960 --> 00:30:22.130 align:middle line:84%
called a consortium
six months ago--

00:30:22.130 --> 00:30:23.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, recently.

00:30:23.030 --> 00:30:26.450 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: --recently, of
the leading physicists

00:30:26.450 --> 00:30:28.040 align:middle line:90%
of the world.

00:30:28.040 --> 00:30:33.090 align:middle line:84%
He called them into the
Vatican, and the discussion

00:30:33.090 --> 00:30:37.370 align:middle line:84%
was about String Theory,
was about quantum physics,

00:30:37.370 --> 00:30:43.360 align:middle line:84%
was about the Big Bang,
what is happening out

00:30:43.360 --> 00:30:46.760 align:middle line:84%
in space, the
universe, the galaxy,

00:30:46.760 --> 00:30:49.160 align:middle line:90%
that seems to be changing.

00:30:49.160 --> 00:30:51.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So as above, so below.

00:30:51.810 --> 00:30:52.830 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: I think so.

00:30:52.830 --> 00:30:55.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then
religion comes and chimes

00:30:55.670 --> 00:30:57.250 align:middle line:84%
in this conversation
that we then

00:30:57.250 --> 00:30:59.430 align:middle line:84%
have heard from
the ancient texts

00:30:59.430 --> 00:31:02.010 align:middle line:84%
and that come in from the
Mayans and the pyramids,

00:31:02.010 --> 00:31:06.630 align:middle line:84%
and all of that seems to align
with this planetary, cosmic,

00:31:06.630 --> 00:31:10.120 align:middle line:84%
galactic conjunction,
essentially, right?

00:31:10.120 --> 00:31:14.090 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: I think so, and it's
probably not a coincidence

00:31:14.090 --> 00:31:18.470 align:middle line:84%
that these events, which
no one could possibly

00:31:18.470 --> 00:31:23.110 align:middle line:84%
think could occur 10 years
ago even, are now happening.

00:31:23.110 --> 00:31:28.650 align:middle line:84%
I think it's all, as some
might say, in divine order.

00:31:28.650 --> 00:31:30.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well now
tell me how this

00:31:30.050 --> 00:31:31.508 align:middle line:84%
relates to us--
what does this have

00:31:31.508 --> 00:31:34.000 align:middle line:84%
to do with how we
relate to each other?

00:31:34.000 --> 00:31:36.290 align:middle line:84%
How is this relevant
to us today?

00:31:36.290 --> 00:31:41.210 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Well, there's two
applied medical procedures

00:31:41.210 --> 00:31:42.950 align:middle line:84%
that are being used
now-- one of them I

00:31:42.950 --> 00:31:45.840 align:middle line:84%
want to talk about is
transcranial magnetic

00:31:45.840 --> 00:31:48.360 align:middle line:90%
stimulation.

00:31:48.360 --> 00:31:52.530 align:middle line:84%
It's been accepted, insurance
companies are paying for it,

00:31:52.530 --> 00:31:57.000 align:middle line:84%
and it's mostly used for
mental health issues, emotions,

00:31:57.000 --> 00:32:02.240 align:middle line:84%
so depression, anxiety,
borderline disorder,

00:32:02.240 --> 00:32:04.280 align:middle line:90%
schizophrenia.

00:32:04.280 --> 00:32:08.310 align:middle line:84%
They put on a helmet, basically,
it's kind of like that,

00:32:08.310 --> 00:32:13.210 align:middle line:84%
with magnets that has a
certain Gauss resonance,

00:32:13.210 --> 00:32:19.130 align:middle line:84%
and that has a direct effect
on the brain chemistry,

00:32:19.130 --> 00:32:25.120 align:middle line:84%
the neurons and so
forth, and they're

00:32:25.120 --> 00:32:26.854 align:middle line:90%
having great success with it.

00:32:26.854 --> 00:32:28.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it shows
that frequency

00:32:28.270 --> 00:32:29.752 align:middle line:84%
has an effect on
brain chemistry.

00:32:29.752 --> 00:32:30.460 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: Exactly.

00:32:30.460 --> 00:32:33.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you're saying
that these particles that

00:32:33.140 --> 00:32:36.520 align:middle line:84%
are coming in that penetrate
our magnetic field actually

00:32:36.520 --> 00:32:38.310 align:middle line:84%
have an effect on
brain chemistry?

00:32:38.310 --> 00:32:41.770 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: I believe so,
it only makes sense.

00:32:41.770 --> 00:32:45.210 align:middle line:84%
We see it in the animal
kingdom-- where it plays,

00:32:45.210 --> 00:32:50.540 align:middle line:84%
perhaps, the most
effect is migrant birds,

00:32:50.540 --> 00:32:53.320 align:middle line:90%
whales that are misdirected.

00:32:53.320 --> 00:33:01.850 align:middle line:84%
Any animal, I'd say any living
thing, that has magnetic grid

00:33:01.850 --> 00:33:05.710 align:middle line:84%
lines as their barometer,
as how they find themselves,

00:33:05.710 --> 00:33:07.850 align:middle line:84%
is definitely affected,
that's been proven.

00:33:07.850 --> 00:33:08.710 align:middle line:90%
No one denies that.

00:33:08.710 --> 00:33:10.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Interesting,
very interesting.

00:33:10.420 --> 00:33:13.600 align:middle line:84%
So this basically could
have-- it's basically

00:33:13.600 --> 00:33:18.510 align:middle line:84%
what EEG would do to the brain,
or its a feedback effect,

00:33:18.510 --> 00:33:19.729 align:middle line:90%
isn't it?

00:33:19.729 --> 00:33:21.770 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: I don't know if
I'd use to the term EEG,

00:33:21.770 --> 00:33:26.510 align:middle line:90%
but something similar to that.

00:33:26.510 --> 00:33:30.080 align:middle line:84%
An EEG IS where we get
readings and so forth, I

00:33:30.080 --> 00:33:35.920 align:middle line:84%
don't know if an EEG has an
effect on the brain chemistry,

00:33:35.920 --> 00:33:39.930 align:middle line:84%
but I do believe this thrust
of magnetic-- of these

00:33:39.930 --> 00:33:43.640 align:middle line:84%
charged particles-- is
playing a role not only

00:33:43.640 --> 00:33:47.835 align:middle line:84%
with natural phenomena,
but I think with us.

00:33:47.835 --> 00:33:48.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's interesting.

00:33:48.960 --> 00:33:52.370 align:middle line:84%
So could this have to do
with a rising of emotions,

00:33:52.370 --> 00:33:56.454 align:middle line:84%
what would this do
to our behavior?

00:33:56.454 --> 00:33:58.120 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Probably a
lot of your audience

00:33:58.120 --> 00:34:02.870 align:middle line:84%
is probably those that
would be described

00:34:02.870 --> 00:34:06.440 align:middle line:84%
as aware and
sensitive to energy,

00:34:06.440 --> 00:34:11.110 align:middle line:84%
and may have this idea of
a wonderful transition,

00:34:11.110 --> 00:34:14.940 align:middle line:84%
they're real excited
about the coming whatever,

00:34:14.940 --> 00:34:21.000 align:middle line:84%
but it might not go
that way for many,

00:34:21.000 --> 00:34:26.909 align:middle line:84%
in the reason for that is that
most people, I would suggest,

00:34:26.909 --> 00:34:29.622 align:middle line:84%
don't like change, even
if it's good change.

00:34:29.622 --> 00:34:30.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Understandably.

00:34:30.580 --> 00:34:33.179 align:middle line:84%
Actually, this makes
a lot of sense, yes.

00:34:33.179 --> 00:34:36.449 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Those that may
an easier time of it

00:34:36.449 --> 00:34:40.190 align:middle line:84%
are simply aware
that change is about

00:34:40.190 --> 00:34:44.440 align:middle line:84%
and can maybe better
flow with things

00:34:44.440 --> 00:34:47.040 align:middle line:84%
that are familiar and
predictable, because it's

00:34:47.040 --> 00:34:49.909 align:middle line:84%
extremely disturbing--
we've all experienced it--

00:34:49.909 --> 00:34:52.130 align:middle line:84%
a breakup of a
relationship, fired

00:34:52.130 --> 00:34:57.230 align:middle line:84%
at work, torn relationships for
one reason or another, things

00:34:57.230 --> 00:35:00.880 align:middle line:84%
not going our way, it can
be extremely disturbing.

00:35:00.880 --> 00:35:05.270 align:middle line:84%
Yet there are some who seem
to just kind of float through.

00:35:05.270 --> 00:35:08.250 align:middle line:84%
I think those people
probably will say, hey,

00:35:08.250 --> 00:35:11.710 align:middle line:84%
let's go for this ride, but
perhaps maybe most of us,

00:35:11.710 --> 00:35:13.350 align:middle line:84%
it will be a bit
more challenging.

00:35:13.350 --> 00:35:15.308 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what's the
good news in all of this?

00:35:15.308 --> 00:35:17.580 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: The good news is
that there is a transition,

00:35:17.580 --> 00:35:19.038 align:middle line:84%
and I think at the
end of the line,

00:35:19.038 --> 00:35:21.430 align:middle line:84%
if a person can simply
tap into themselves

00:35:21.430 --> 00:35:24.180 align:middle line:84%
and simply stay as
true as they can

00:35:24.180 --> 00:35:27.660 align:middle line:84%
to their integrity-- not
going to be easy for many--

00:35:27.660 --> 00:35:31.690 align:middle line:84%
but I guess, in part, it's
back to faith and belief

00:35:31.690 --> 00:35:36.430 align:middle line:84%
that this is part of something,
it's part of a process.

00:35:36.430 --> 00:35:38.970 align:middle line:84%
That's why I find
comfort in my science,

00:35:38.970 --> 00:35:41.530 align:middle line:84%
with cyclical events--
this is part of a cycle.

00:35:41.530 --> 00:35:43.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, there's
a cycle that's

00:35:43.030 --> 00:35:45.029 align:middle line:84%
coming upon us right now
with the Venus transit,

00:35:45.029 --> 00:35:47.100 align:middle line:84%
and it's something that's
happening right now,

00:35:47.100 --> 00:35:49.904 align:middle line:90%
during the filming of this show.

00:35:49.904 --> 00:35:52.320 align:middle line:84%
Tell us a little bit about
it-- what is the Venus transit?

00:35:52.320 --> 00:35:53.486 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: I'm feeling it now.

00:35:53.486 --> 00:35:55.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And how does it
affect us-- right, exactly.

00:35:55.700 --> 00:35:56.699 align:middle line:90%
Talking about feelings.

00:35:56.699 --> 00:35:58.115 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Venus is
the love planet.

00:35:58.115 --> 00:36:01.550 align:middle line:90%


00:36:01.550 --> 00:36:03.780 align:middle line:84%
Like so many things with
cyclical events, and this

00:36:03.780 --> 00:36:07.280 align:middle line:84%
being the Venus transit,
I would say it's something

00:36:07.280 --> 00:36:11.800 align:middle line:90%
similar to December 21, 2012.

00:36:11.800 --> 00:36:14.450 align:middle line:84%
Many people think that
it's like a light switch--

00:36:14.450 --> 00:36:16.370 align:middle line:90%
you hit it and you feel it.

00:36:16.370 --> 00:36:22.600 align:middle line:84%
The transit-- just like with
the date of Mayan 2012--

00:36:22.600 --> 00:36:24.490 align:middle line:90%
is that it's a process.

00:36:24.490 --> 00:36:31.060 align:middle line:84%
The Venus transit, if it's
related to astrological effects

00:36:31.060 --> 00:36:32.890 align:middle line:84%
and meaning, it
would be a process.

00:36:32.890 --> 00:36:35.265 align:middle line:84%
In other words, anything that
would have happened already

00:36:35.265 --> 00:36:38.050 align:middle line:84%
is and will happen
even more after.

00:36:38.050 --> 00:36:43.420 align:middle line:84%
In the science community,
they don't necessarily

00:36:43.420 --> 00:36:48.090 align:middle line:84%
see it in the way of
astrology or something

00:36:48.090 --> 00:36:50.750 align:middle line:90%
that a person would feel.

00:36:50.750 --> 00:36:54.010 align:middle line:90%
They find great meaning in this.

00:36:54.010 --> 00:36:57.630 align:middle line:84%
Because of the Venus
transit, what it does

00:36:57.630 --> 00:36:59.510 align:middle line:84%
is a couple things--
one is it gives them

00:36:59.510 --> 00:37:02.800 align:middle line:84%
more information
about Venus itself.

00:37:02.800 --> 00:37:06.560 align:middle line:84%
Right now there's a space
ship called the Venus

00:37:06.560 --> 00:37:07.850 align:middle line:90%
Express Satellite--

00:37:07.850 --> 00:37:09.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, right.

00:37:09.170 --> 00:37:12.510 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: --that's perched
perfectly right now to gather

00:37:12.510 --> 00:37:16.620 align:middle line:84%
incredible information,
but even more meaningful

00:37:16.620 --> 00:37:22.070 align:middle line:84%
is that it gives
scientists an opportunity,

00:37:22.070 --> 00:37:25.420 align:middle line:84%
because of the
shadow it creates,

00:37:25.420 --> 00:37:26.979 align:middle line:90%
to look for other planets.

00:37:26.979 --> 00:37:28.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What we're
seeing here is basically

00:37:28.770 --> 00:37:31.150 align:middle line:84%
where you'll able
to see this from

00:37:31.150 --> 00:37:33.410 align:middle line:84%
and what the Venus transit
is, but let's take a look

00:37:33.410 --> 00:37:35.380 align:middle line:84%
at the video so
that people can get

00:37:35.380 --> 00:37:38.027 align:middle line:84%
a clear idea of exactly
what the Venus transit is.

00:37:38.027 --> 00:37:39.110 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look at this.

00:37:39.110 --> 00:37:46.890 align:middle line:90%


00:37:46.890 --> 00:37:49.150 align:middle line:84%
>>ANNOUNCER: The 2012
transit of Venus,

00:37:49.150 --> 00:37:52.410 align:middle line:90%
presented by Science at NASA.

00:37:52.410 --> 00:37:56.800 align:middle line:84%
One little black spot on the sun
sure can cause a lot of fuss.

00:37:56.800 --> 00:38:00.340 align:middle line:84%
Twice every 120 years,
Venus passes directly

00:38:00.340 --> 00:38:02.310 align:middle line:90%
in front of the sun.

00:38:02.310 --> 00:38:04.940 align:middle line:84%
The circular spot the planet
makes on the solar disk

00:38:04.940 --> 00:38:07.840 align:middle line:84%
is not much bigger than
an ordinary sunspot,

00:38:07.840 --> 00:38:11.770 align:middle line:84%
but every time it happens,
it is a worldwide sensation.

00:38:11.770 --> 00:38:15.330 align:middle line:84%
The next transit of
Venus is on June 5, 2012,

00:38:15.330 --> 00:38:17.560 align:middle line:84%
and for the first time
since the 19th century,

00:38:17.560 --> 00:38:20.780 align:middle line:84%
the event will be visible
across all of North America.

00:38:20.780 --> 00:38:24.490 align:middle line:84%
The nearly seven-hour transit
begins at 3:09 PM Pacific

00:38:24.490 --> 00:38:25.850 align:middle line:90%
Daylight Time.

00:38:25.850 --> 00:38:29.400 align:middle line:84%
Observers on seven continents,
even a sliver of Antarctica,

00:38:29.400 --> 00:38:31.290 align:middle line:90%
will be able to see it.

00:38:31.290 --> 00:38:33.280 align:middle line:84%
Across the United
States, the transit

00:38:33.280 --> 00:38:35.870 align:middle line:84%
is at its best around
sunset, a rare photo

00:38:35.870 --> 00:38:38.460 align:middle line:90%
op for creative photographers.

00:38:38.460 --> 00:38:42.690 align:middle line:84%
Observing tip-- do
not stare at the sun.

00:38:42.690 --> 00:38:44.760 align:middle line:84%
Venus covers too little
of the solar disk

00:38:44.760 --> 00:38:46.950 align:middle line:90%
to block the blinding glare.

00:38:46.950 --> 00:38:49.350 align:middle line:84%
Instead, use some type
of protection technique

00:38:49.350 --> 00:38:50.620 align:middle line:90%
or solar filter.

00:38:50.620 --> 00:38:54.390 align:middle line:84%
A Number 14 welder's
glass is a good choice.

00:38:54.390 --> 00:38:57.610 align:middle line:84%
For some observers, the view
provides an unsettling sense

00:38:57.610 --> 00:38:58.630 align:middle line:90%
of scale.

00:38:58.630 --> 00:39:02.300 align:middle line:84%
Venus seems so small and
fragile against the solar disc.

00:39:02.300 --> 00:39:05.200 align:middle line:84%
Our own planet is
equally minuscule.

00:39:05.200 --> 00:39:07.220 align:middle line:84%
Others say it looks like
a black hole punched

00:39:07.220 --> 00:39:10.760 align:middle line:84%
in the surface of the
sun-- very strange.

00:39:10.760 --> 00:39:13.290 align:middle line:84%
Transits of Venus first
gained worldwide attention

00:39:13.290 --> 00:39:15.750 align:middle line:84%
in the 18th century, when
one of the biggest mysteries

00:39:15.750 --> 00:39:18.940 align:middle line:84%
of science was the size
of the solar system.

00:39:18.940 --> 00:39:21.680 align:middle line:84%
It might seem amazing
today, but astronomers

00:39:21.680 --> 00:39:24.010 align:middle line:84%
didn't know the absolute
distance between any two

00:39:24.010 --> 00:39:25.290 align:middle line:90%
planets.

00:39:25.290 --> 00:39:29.190 align:middle line:84%
How many miles would you have to
travel to reach another world?

00:39:29.190 --> 00:39:31.250 align:middle line:84%
The answer was as
mysterious then

00:39:31.250 --> 00:39:33.880 align:middle line:84%
as the nature of
dark energy is now.

00:39:33.880 --> 00:39:37.760 align:middle line:10%
Venus was the key, according
to astronomer Sir Edmund Haley.

00:39:37.760 --> 00:39:39.650 align:middle line:10%
He realized that by
observing transits

00:39:39.650 --> 00:39:42.200 align:middle line:10%
from widely spaced
locations on Earth,

00:39:42.200 --> 00:39:46.330 align:middle line:10%
it should be possible to
triangulate distance to Venus.

00:39:46.330 --> 00:39:48.410 align:middle line:84%
The idea galvanized
scientists, who

00:39:48.410 --> 00:39:50.510 align:middle line:84%
set off on expeditions
around the world

00:39:50.510 --> 00:39:53.990 align:middle line:84%
to view a pair of
transits in the 1760s.

00:39:53.990 --> 00:39:56.500 align:middle line:84%
The great explorer James
Cook himself was dispatched

00:39:56.500 --> 00:39:58.440 align:middle line:84%
to observe one from
Tahiti, a place

00:39:58.440 --> 00:40:03.230 align:middle line:84%
as alien to 18th century
Europeans as the moon or Mars.

00:40:03.230 --> 00:40:06.070 align:middle line:84%
Historians have called the
international effort the Apollo

00:40:06.070 --> 00:40:08.210 align:middle line:90%
Program of the 18th century.

00:40:08.210 --> 00:40:10.620 align:middle line:84%
In retrospect, it
falls into the category

00:40:10.620 --> 00:40:13.910 align:middle line:84%
of things that only
sounded like a good idea.

00:40:13.910 --> 00:40:17.470 align:middle line:84%
Bad weather, primitive optics,
and the natural fuzziness

00:40:17.470 --> 00:40:19.660 align:middle line:84%
of Venus' atmosphere
prevented observers

00:40:19.660 --> 00:40:22.070 align:middle line:84%
from gathering the
data they needed.

00:40:22.070 --> 00:40:24.880 align:middle line:84%
The distance to Venus was not
measured with high precision

00:40:24.880 --> 00:40:28.370 align:middle line:84%
until two centuries later,
when astronomers of the 1960s

00:40:28.370 --> 00:40:30.740 align:middle line:90%
pinged the planet with radar.

00:40:30.740 --> 00:40:34.010 align:middle line:84%
This year's transit is the
second of an eight-year pair.

00:40:34.010 --> 00:40:36.500 align:middle line:84%
Anticipation was
high in June, 2004,

00:40:36.500 --> 00:40:38.580 align:middle line:90%
as Venus approached the sun.

00:40:38.580 --> 00:40:40.980 align:middle line:84%
No one alive at the time
had seen a transit of Venus

00:40:40.980 --> 00:40:43.760 align:middle line:84%
with their own eyes, and the
hand drawn sketches and grainy

00:40:43.760 --> 00:40:46.050 align:middle line:84%
photos of the previous
centuries scarcely

00:40:46.050 --> 00:40:48.620 align:middle line:84%
prepared them for what
was about to happen.

00:40:48.620 --> 00:40:51.650 align:middle line:84%
Modern solar telescopes
captured an unprecedented view

00:40:51.650 --> 00:40:55.160 align:middle line:84%
of Venus' atmosphere
back lit by solar fire.

00:40:55.160 --> 00:40:57.590 align:middle line:84%
They saw Venus transiting
the sun's ghostly corona

00:40:57.590 --> 00:40:59.810 align:middle line:84%
and gliding past magnetic
filaments big enough

00:40:59.810 --> 00:41:02.120 align:middle line:90%
to swallow the whole planet.

00:41:02.120 --> 00:41:05.320 align:middle line:84%
One photographer even caught
a spaceship, the International

00:41:05.320 --> 00:41:09.790 align:middle line:84%
Space Station, transiting
the sun alongside Venus.

00:41:09.790 --> 00:41:13.160 align:middle line:84%
2012 should be even better, as
cameras and solar telescopes

00:41:13.160 --> 00:41:14.750 align:middle line:90%
have improved.

00:41:14.750 --> 00:41:17.105 align:middle line:84%
Moreover, NASA's Solar
Dynamics Observatory

00:41:17.105 --> 00:41:19.700 align:middle line:90%
is going to be watching, too.

00:41:19.700 --> 00:41:23.820 align:middle line:84%
SDO will produce Hubble quality
images of this a rare event.

00:41:23.820 --> 00:41:28.440 align:middle line:84%
Apparently, one little black dot
really is worth all the fuss.

00:41:28.440 --> 00:41:31.252 align:middle line:84%
For more observing tips
and links to live webcasts,

00:41:31.252 --> 00:41:32.210 align:middle line:90%
visit science.nasa.gov.

