what you're going to be seeing.

00:44:31.560 --> 00:44:33.143 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Participate
in it-- just know

00:44:33.143 --> 00:44:35.557 align:middle line:84%
that billions
around the world are

00:44:35.557 --> 00:44:37.140 align:middle line:84%
going to be looking
at the same thing.

00:44:37.140 --> 00:44:40.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So Venus is passing
between the Earth and the sun.

00:44:40.460 --> 00:44:41.500 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: That's right.

00:44:41.500 --> 00:44:43.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: OK, and
so now, does this

00:44:43.600 --> 00:44:45.350 align:middle line:84%
have anything to do
with the Earth changes

00:44:45.350 --> 00:44:46.975 align:middle line:84%
that we're talking
about, or could this

00:44:46.975 --> 00:44:49.830 align:middle line:84%
have anything to do
with the polarization

00:44:49.830 --> 00:44:51.350 align:middle line:90%
that we were talking about?

00:44:51.350 --> 00:44:53.250 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: Not that I'm aware of.

00:44:53.250 --> 00:44:54.690 align:middle line:84%
There are some
people who believe

00:44:54.690 --> 00:44:56.720 align:middle line:84%
when there's planetary
alignments, that that

00:44:56.720 --> 00:44:59.090 align:middle line:90%
causes Earth changing events.

00:44:59.090 --> 00:45:01.870 align:middle line:84%
This is what I know--
the scientific data says

00:45:01.870 --> 00:45:05.750 align:middle line:84%
that the alignment
of a full moon,

00:45:05.750 --> 00:45:08.090 align:middle line:84%
just our full moon
and the Earth,

00:45:08.090 --> 00:45:13.740 align:middle line:84%
has 100 times more effect on,
in this case would be water

00:45:13.740 --> 00:45:18.840 align:middle line:84%
displacement, tides, than
all nine planets lined up.

00:45:18.840 --> 00:45:24.820 align:middle line:84%
So I can't say no--
I'm open to whatever.

00:45:24.820 --> 00:45:30.780 align:middle line:84%
I mean what happens if it
happens to be in the way of--

00:45:30.780 --> 00:45:32.910 align:middle line:84%
and then what kind
of effect that has,

00:45:32.910 --> 00:45:34.694 align:middle line:90%
I don't know if anybody knows.

00:45:34.694 --> 00:45:36.110 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Are there
any particular--

00:45:36.110 --> 00:45:38.970 align:middle line:84%
are there solar flares
going on all the time?

00:45:38.970 --> 00:45:42.200 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Yes, yesterday
or day before yesterday,

00:45:42.200 --> 00:45:46.950 align:middle line:84%
there was an M-3 Class flare,
and a following coronal mass

00:45:46.950 --> 00:45:48.390 align:middle line:90%
ejection that followed.

00:45:48.390 --> 00:45:49.430 align:middle line:90%
It's happening now.

00:45:49.430 --> 00:45:51.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's happening
all the time.

00:45:51.030 --> 00:45:52.990 align:middle line:84%
One of the Facebook
questions coming in

00:45:52.990 --> 00:45:55.400 align:middle line:84%
is asking if they
have a magnetic bed

00:45:55.400 --> 00:45:58.420 align:middle line:84%
or if they use magnets
like magnetic therapy,

00:45:58.420 --> 00:46:00.960 align:middle line:84%
could this affect them
when these solar flares

00:46:00.960 --> 00:46:03.880 align:middle line:84%
and these particles come
charging in to the magnetic--

00:46:03.880 --> 00:46:05.700 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Good
question-- I would like

00:46:05.700 --> 00:46:08.510 align:middle line:90%
to think in a positive way.

00:46:08.510 --> 00:46:10.830 align:middle line:90%
I'm all for magnetic therapy.

00:46:10.830 --> 00:46:13.960 align:middle line:84%
Those of you that are familiar
with Reiki and acupuncture,

00:46:13.960 --> 00:46:17.280 align:middle line:84%
acupuncture really
explains it all.

00:46:17.280 --> 00:46:20.860 align:middle line:84%
What acupuncture says is we have
a magnetic field that surrounds

00:46:20.860 --> 00:46:26.810 align:middle line:84%
our bodies, and then there's
the energy points, meridians,

00:46:26.810 --> 00:46:29.440 align:middle line:84%
and by the acupuncturist
manipulating

00:46:29.440 --> 00:46:31.820 align:middle line:84%
particular meridians,
depending on the element,

00:46:31.820 --> 00:46:34.164 align:middle line:84%
it brings balance
back to the body.

00:46:34.164 --> 00:46:35.580 align:middle line:84%
That's the good
news-- that's what

00:46:35.580 --> 00:46:38.120 align:middle line:84%
I think this is all
about-- you asked earlier.

00:46:38.120 --> 00:46:40.760 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to think that
my hypothesis would

00:46:40.760 --> 00:46:43.900 align:middle line:84%
be that it's going
to bring not only us,

00:46:43.900 --> 00:46:48.872 align:middle line:84%
but the earth, Gaia, back to
balance-- we're out of balance.

00:46:48.872 --> 00:46:50.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, now, exactly
how would that work?

00:46:50.830 --> 00:46:52.207 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: Tipped over.

00:46:52.207 --> 00:46:54.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Exactly, but that is
the point, that is actually

00:46:54.540 --> 00:46:57.500 align:middle line:84%
the point that many have
made, that this brings us

00:46:57.500 --> 00:46:59.650 align:middle line:84%
back together in
many different ways.

00:46:59.650 --> 00:47:01.600 align:middle line:84%
It brings us together
in our communities,

00:47:01.600 --> 00:47:04.650 align:middle line:84%
but how does it
correct us from being

00:47:04.650 --> 00:47:09.460 align:middle line:84%
off balance from a
perspective of our poles?

00:47:09.460 --> 00:47:12.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: I believe all
my research suggests--

00:47:12.500 --> 00:47:14.900 align:middle line:84%
I have two books, and I'm
working on the third--

00:47:14.900 --> 00:47:19.900 align:middle line:84%
that it's charged particles
that are the conduit.

00:47:19.900 --> 00:47:23.710 align:middle line:84%
Now, the Mayans call it ether,
they call it the new energy,

00:47:23.710 --> 00:47:27.390 align:middle line:84%
which ether is really not new,
but the way they describe it,

00:47:27.390 --> 00:47:28.240 align:middle line:90%
it is new.

00:47:28.240 --> 00:47:31.780 align:middle line:84%
Basically, if you
translate the language,

00:47:31.780 --> 00:47:35.160 align:middle line:84%
it's the space between space
is how they describe it.

00:47:35.160 --> 00:47:39.154 align:middle line:84%
Well, yes guess who showed up
at the Vatican-- scientists

00:47:39.154 --> 00:47:40.820 align:middle line:84%
from all over the
world who were talking

00:47:40.820 --> 00:47:43.020 align:middle line:90%
about the space between space.

00:47:43.020 --> 00:47:44.320 align:middle line:90%
Is there a connection?

00:47:44.320 --> 00:47:44.850 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:47:44.850 --> 00:47:46.974 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So I see there's
many ways that it actually

00:47:46.974 --> 00:47:47.934 align:middle line:90%
can connect us.

00:47:47.934 --> 00:47:49.850 align:middle line:84%
So you don't believe
that anything significant

00:47:49.850 --> 00:47:53.545 align:middle line:84%
is going to happen, actually,
on the day of December 21, 2012.

00:47:53.545 --> 00:47:54.350 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: No.

00:47:54.350 --> 00:47:57.174 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And why
do you think that?

00:47:57.174 --> 00:47:58.590 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Well, I
can only tell you

00:47:58.590 --> 00:48:01.090 align:middle line:84%
that that's what every
Mayan elder that I've ever

00:48:01.090 --> 00:48:02.720 align:middle line:84%
interviewed or spoken
to has told me,

00:48:02.720 --> 00:48:06.730 align:middle line:84%
and I have no reason to disagree
with it-- it makes sense,

00:48:06.730 --> 00:48:08.740 align:middle line:84%
such as the harmonic
convergence, or even

00:48:08.740 --> 00:48:10.580 align:middle line:90%
today with the Venus transit.

00:48:10.580 --> 00:48:12.346 align:middle line:84%
Nothing-- well,
for some of you--

00:48:12.346 --> 00:48:15.010 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Earth-shattering
is happening.

00:48:15.010 --> 00:48:16.800 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: But what's
being lost in that,

00:48:16.800 --> 00:48:18.790 align:middle line:84%
because of Hollywood
and so forth,

00:48:18.790 --> 00:48:21.660 align:middle line:84%
is that the process
has already begun.

00:48:21.660 --> 00:48:25.127 align:middle line:84%
This is-- it's a window, and
you go through this transition,

00:48:25.127 --> 00:48:27.460 align:middle line:84%
that's what-- matter of fact,
that's the Mayan word they

00:48:27.460 --> 00:48:30.260 align:middle line:84%
use-- transition, and we're
in the transition now.

00:48:30.260 --> 00:48:32.530 align:middle line:84%
There's going to be
some up and downs,

00:48:32.530 --> 00:48:34.840 align:middle line:84%
and maybe you might
have a peak experience,

00:48:34.840 --> 00:48:37.830 align:middle line:84%
but I doubt it's going
to be on that day.

00:48:37.830 --> 00:48:41.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you've spend a
lot of time with these Hopis

00:48:41.400 --> 00:48:44.700 align:middle line:84%
and shamans, and
people telling you this

00:48:44.700 --> 00:48:45.700 align:middle line:90%
is not necessarily true.

00:48:45.700 --> 00:48:47.720 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: I have.

00:48:47.720 --> 00:48:49.680 align:middle line:84%
This is just one of my
uniforms-- believe me,

00:48:49.680 --> 00:48:55.310 align:middle line:84%
folks, I dress down, and I
get right in there with them.

00:48:55.310 --> 00:48:58.420 align:middle line:84%
Try fasting for three days,
that's a religious experience.

00:48:58.420 --> 00:49:00.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So how long
would we expect something

00:49:00.520 --> 00:49:02.290 align:middle line:90%
like this to last?

00:49:02.290 --> 00:49:05.620 align:middle line:90%
Does it go into 2013, 2014?

00:49:05.620 --> 00:49:08.750 align:middle line:84%
One of our listeners is
actually even saying 2016?

00:49:08.750 --> 00:49:11.220 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Well, there's a lot
of controversy about that,

00:49:11.220 --> 00:49:13.330 align:middle line:84%
and even some of
the what I believe

00:49:13.330 --> 00:49:17.690 align:middle line:84%
to be highly esteemed elders
who are knowledgeable,

00:49:17.690 --> 00:49:20.120 align:middle line:84%
think that the bad
stuff, if you want

00:49:20.120 --> 00:49:28.990 align:middle line:84%
to call it that, the big shift,
may not occur until 2050.

00:49:28.990 --> 00:49:32.650 align:middle line:84%
I've heard 2015, 2016,
I really can't say.

00:49:32.650 --> 00:49:36.420 align:middle line:84%
I think the
transition has begun.

00:49:36.420 --> 00:49:38.410 align:middle line:90%
Check back with me in a year.

00:49:38.410 --> 00:49:40.760 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I don't see a lot
of fear are coming from you.

00:49:40.760 --> 00:49:43.270 align:middle line:84%
I don't see a lot of
conspiracy theory coming

00:49:43.270 --> 00:49:44.780 align:middle line:90%
from what you have to say here.

00:49:44.780 --> 00:49:47.530 align:middle line:84%
I see what you have to
say as fairly scientific,

00:49:47.530 --> 00:49:51.720 align:middle line:84%
and has been validated
by NASA and other people,

00:49:51.720 --> 00:49:54.210 align:middle line:84%
other organizations,
scientific organizations,

00:49:54.210 --> 00:49:56.100 align:middle line:84%
have endorsed your
work, haven't they?

00:49:56.100 --> 00:49:57.640 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: Oh, yes they have.

00:49:57.640 --> 00:50:00.920 align:middle line:84%
The effect former director of
NOAA, the space weather center,

00:50:00.920 --> 00:50:05.020 align:middle line:84%
Doctor Hildner, the
deputy director of SOHO,

00:50:05.020 --> 00:50:09.170 align:middle line:84%
the European Space Agency,
the leading director

00:50:09.170 --> 00:50:14.200 align:middle line:84%
at the Royal Observatory,
Tom van Flandern

00:50:14.200 --> 00:50:18.420 align:middle line:84%
of the US Naval Observatory--
yeah, these are heavy hitters.

00:50:18.420 --> 00:50:20.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And do those
organizations say that there's

00:50:20.640 --> 00:50:24.690 align:middle line:84%
going to be a big shift,
and if so, what would it be?

00:50:24.690 --> 00:50:27.950 align:middle line:90%


00:50:27.950 --> 00:50:31.580 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Not as of
this date, and I

00:50:31.580 --> 00:50:33.630 align:middle line:84%
don't think it would
be wise for them to.

00:50:33.630 --> 00:50:35.440 align:middle line:84%
They really need to
be careful with this.

00:50:35.440 --> 00:50:44.930 align:middle line:84%
I had a big discussion of
omission versus disclosure--

00:50:44.930 --> 00:50:48.100 align:middle line:84%
omission versus
disclosure-- and whether it

00:50:48.100 --> 00:50:53.137 align:middle line:84%
be 9/11 or Katrina or these
big significant events, what

00:50:53.137 --> 00:50:55.470 align:middle line:84%
is better for the population--
omission, in other words,

00:50:55.470 --> 00:50:59.990 align:middle line:84%
keep it down, or disclosure,
let the people handle it, tell

00:50:59.990 --> 00:51:01.550 align:middle line:90%
them the truth.

00:51:01.550 --> 00:51:02.940 align:middle line:90%
I'm not sure what the answer is.

00:51:02.940 --> 00:51:06.220 align:middle line:84%
I lean towards
disclosure myself.

00:51:06.220 --> 00:51:07.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ultimately, yes.

00:51:07.560 --> 00:51:10.970 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: That's-- my audience,
probably your audience--

00:51:10.970 --> 00:51:14.930 align:middle line:84%
I just got that-- you know,
I think other countries would

00:51:14.930 --> 00:51:21.000 align:middle line:84%
definitely have a better
adjustment then we would.

00:51:21.000 --> 00:51:23.060 align:middle line:84%
We are the most advanced
country in the world,

00:51:23.060 --> 00:51:25.360 align:middle line:84%
that's like a
double edged sword.

00:51:25.360 --> 00:51:28.310 align:middle line:84%
We've got the technology
that's second to none,

00:51:28.310 --> 00:51:30.357 align:middle line:84%
but we've gotten
dumbed down a bit.

00:51:30.357 --> 00:51:31.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: In what way,
what do you mean?

00:51:31.940 --> 00:51:35.240 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: I don't think
our intuitive nature,

00:51:35.240 --> 00:51:42.190 align:middle line:84%
our true senses is working,
is firing on all cylinders.

00:51:42.190 --> 00:51:46.950 align:middle line:84%
I think we've kind of--
technology has its advantages,

00:51:46.950 --> 00:51:51.030 align:middle line:84%
but I think it takes away
from our natural abilities.

00:51:51.030 --> 00:51:52.620 align:middle line:84%
For example, the
animals-- I think

00:51:52.620 --> 00:51:57.230 align:middle line:84%
animals can sense earthquakes
or something coming,

00:51:57.230 --> 00:51:58.430 align:middle line:90%
and they know what to do.

00:51:58.430 --> 00:52:01.020 align:middle line:84%
I think we used
to have that, too.

00:52:01.020 --> 00:52:03.560 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: You only speak from
some type of experience.

00:52:03.560 --> 00:52:05.660 align:middle line:84%
Have you seen
this, where there's

00:52:05.660 --> 00:52:09.440 align:middle line:84%
technologies or intuitions
that are available to us

00:52:09.440 --> 00:52:12.720 align:middle line:84%
that we don't necessarily
tap into on a regular basis?

00:52:12.720 --> 00:52:16.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Every day, and
I'm guilty of it myself.

00:52:16.500 --> 00:52:18.360 align:middle line:84%
If I don't have my
cell phone with me,

00:52:18.360 --> 00:52:20.580 align:middle line:84%
if I'm not texting,
if I'm not online,

00:52:20.580 --> 00:52:25.550 align:middle line:84%
if I'm not writing questions
into Facebook, I'm lost, right?

00:52:25.550 --> 00:52:27.640 align:middle line:84%
We fill every day
with such technology,

00:52:27.640 --> 00:52:28.790 align:middle line:90%
but where's the interplay?

00:52:28.790 --> 00:52:29.984 align:middle line:90%
Do you know your neighbors?

00:52:29.984 --> 00:52:31.900 align:middle line:84%
How many of you can tell
me who your neighbors

00:52:31.900 --> 00:52:32.950 align:middle line:90%
on your left and your right?

00:52:32.950 --> 00:52:35.575 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, when we have this
amazing technology out in space

00:52:35.575 --> 00:52:38.190 align:middle line:84%
that can literally
take a picture of Mars

00:52:38.190 --> 00:52:42.760 align:middle line:84%
and transmit it back to
us, and these are just

00:52:42.760 --> 00:52:44.120 align:middle line:90%
incredible technologies.

00:52:44.120 --> 00:52:47.760 align:middle line:84%
If you look at things like that
from a scientific perspective,

00:52:47.760 --> 00:52:51.650 align:middle line:84%
it makes sense to consume
that information instead.

00:52:51.650 --> 00:52:53.200 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Absolutelt--
again, there's

00:52:53.200 --> 00:52:58.210 align:middle line:84%
the marriage of the
two, and the escalation

00:52:58.210 --> 00:53:00.725 align:middle line:84%
of Earth changing events
that I believe are happening.

00:53:00.725 --> 00:53:05.400 align:middle line:90%


00:53:05.400 --> 00:53:08.387 align:middle line:84%
I think that's its purpose,
is the Earth changing events--

00:53:08.387 --> 00:53:09.970 align:middle line:84%
earthquakes, volcanoes,
and so forth--

00:53:09.970 --> 00:53:11.345 align:middle line:84%
there is a pattern
of escalation.

00:53:11.345 --> 00:53:13.220 align:middle line:84%
I believe it's going to
continue for a while,

00:53:13.220 --> 00:53:14.380 align:middle line:90%
it's part of the process.

00:53:14.380 --> 00:53:16.600 align:middle line:84%
I don't see it as
punishment, I don't see it

00:53:16.600 --> 00:53:22.350 align:middle line:84%
as trying to hurt us and
that we're bringing it on.

00:53:22.350 --> 00:53:25.000 align:middle line:84%
I think-- well, actually,
we might be bringing it on--

00:53:25.000 --> 00:53:29.330 align:middle line:84%
that it's here to
help us, that maybe

00:53:29.330 --> 00:53:33.120 align:middle line:84%
if something was to occur that
disrupts our Facebook and all

00:53:33.120 --> 00:53:36.260 align:middle line:84%
this stuff, that maybe we
might meet our neighbors,

00:53:36.260 --> 00:53:39.000 align:middle line:84%
and maybe we might find
that we need each other,

00:53:39.000 --> 00:53:40.540 align:middle line:84%
and maybe we might
develop something

00:53:40.540 --> 00:53:43.570 align:middle line:90%
called a community, family.

00:53:43.570 --> 00:53:45.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, one of our
Facebook questions coming in

00:53:45.880 --> 00:53:49.620 align:middle line:84%
is saying-- Margie is saying
if there is an actual pole

00:53:49.620 --> 00:53:52.700 align:middle line:84%
shift that happens, will the
North and the South Poles

00:53:52.700 --> 00:53:53.290 align:middle line:90%
shift?

00:53:53.290 --> 00:53:54.000 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: Yes.

00:53:54.000 --> 00:53:56.416 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Then when we get to
know all sorts of communities.

00:53:56.416 --> 00:54:00.990 align:middle line:90%


00:54:00.990 --> 00:54:04.810 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Margie,
there is a pole shift,

00:54:04.810 --> 00:54:07.800 align:middle line:84%
but that is not
crustal displacement.

00:54:07.800 --> 00:54:11.461 align:middle line:84%
The earth is not going to flip,
the magnetic pole will flip,

00:54:11.461 --> 00:54:12.460 align:middle line:90%
and that is significant.

00:54:12.460 --> 00:54:13.793 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What if that mean to us?

00:54:13.793 --> 00:54:16.400 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: That means that
the weather patterns

00:54:16.400 --> 00:54:18.545 align:middle line:90%
will change significantly.

00:54:18.545 --> 00:54:21.160 align:middle line:84%
It's a pattern of
events that take up,

00:54:21.160 --> 00:54:24.260 align:middle line:84%
geographically, a very
short period of time,

00:54:24.260 --> 00:54:25.580 align:middle line:90%
but to us may seem longer.

00:54:25.580 --> 00:54:29.000 align:middle line:84%
It could happen within
a 44-year period,

00:54:29.000 --> 00:54:33.940 align:middle line:84%
and what we would see is the
magnetic north bouncing around,

00:54:33.940 --> 00:54:36.100 align:middle line:84%
maybe at first just
over to Canada or--

00:54:36.100 --> 00:54:37.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What would
that look like, though?

00:54:37.850 --> 00:54:38.891 align:middle line:90%
How would that affect us?

00:54:38.891 --> 00:54:43.944 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Literally, airlines,
anybody with GPS services,

00:54:43.944 --> 00:54:46.110 align:middle line:84%
all the satellites and
airlines and so on, they have

00:54:46.110 --> 00:54:48.789 align:middle line:84%
to recalibrate their
instruments all the time--

00:54:48.789 --> 00:54:49.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Constantly.

00:54:49.580 --> 00:54:52.597 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Constantly, because
the magnetic pole is shifting.

00:54:52.597 --> 00:54:53.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: They do right now?

00:54:53.680 --> 00:54:54.730 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: They do right now.

00:54:54.730 --> 00:54:55.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting--

00:54:55.400 --> 00:54:56.191 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: Right now.

00:54:56.191 --> 00:54:58.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And this is all because
of the solar activity cutting

00:54:58.880 --> 00:55:02.904 align:middle line:84%
through the magnetic field,
going down and creating

00:55:02.904 --> 00:55:04.570 align:middle line:84%
that resonant effect,
so this is really,

00:55:04.570 --> 00:55:06.540 align:middle line:90%
truly affecting the grids.

00:55:06.540 --> 00:55:08.750 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: It is, all
as part of a cycle.

00:55:08.750 --> 00:55:11.830 align:middle line:84%
We've seen it-- the earth has
seen this many times before--

00:55:11.830 --> 00:55:14.241 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: But it's
not catastrophic.

00:55:14.241 --> 00:55:15.240 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: The pole shift?

00:55:15.240 --> 00:55:15.823 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:55:15.823 --> 00:55:16.710 align:middle line:90%
>>MITCH: No.

00:55:16.710 --> 00:55:18.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: But the climate changes?

00:55:18.840 --> 00:55:21.780 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: That could
be significant.

00:55:21.780 --> 00:55:25.294 align:middle line:84%
Right now, we're going through
not a pleasant warming trend,

00:55:25.294 --> 00:55:26.710 align:middle line:84%
but I think it's
going to be worse

00:55:26.710 --> 00:55:28.209 align:middle line:84%
when the cooling
trend comes myself.

00:55:28.209 --> 00:55:31.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is there
anything specific

00:55:31.720 --> 00:55:35.070 align:middle line:84%
that you do in your life to
prepare for any-- with all

00:55:35.070 --> 00:55:36.799 align:middle line:84%
of your knowledge
and everything?

00:55:36.799 --> 00:55:38.590 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: Well, you
know, I met my neighbors

00:55:38.590 --> 00:55:41.246 align:middle line:90%
for the first time.

00:55:41.246 --> 00:55:43.370 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That was the last
time I saw my neighbors--

00:55:43.370 --> 00:55:45.411 align:middle line:84%
>>MITCH: I hope I have
one minute at to leave you

00:55:45.411 --> 00:55:49.740 align:middle line:84%
with this-- I worked
with the Red Cross

00:55:49.740 --> 00:55:51.430 align:middle line:84%
and I worked with
FEMA, and I'll never

00:55:51.430 --> 00:55:55.970 align:middle line:84%
